<br>
   All in all, I think it was a wonderful companion to the novel.  Sure, some parts (great parts) of the book had to be cut out of the movie, or others shortened, but all in all I was very happy with it.  The parts that weren't in the movie mostly consisted of stuff I have no trouble imagining (farmer maggot's role in the movie, for example, is tiny, but when I read the book, I had no trouble whatsoever imagining what their reunion would be like).<br>
<br>
